    <h1>Company History</h1>
    <br>
    <h3>1979</h3>
    <p>When McDonalds first arrived in Singapore, they opened their first outlet at the Liat Towers located on Orchard Road, setting a record for the most hamburgers served in a day.</p>
    <br>
    <h3>1982</h3>
    <p>East Coast Park welcomes McDonalds first Drive-Thru, granting access to another way to get food from McDonalds. This same outlet would later get Singapore's first Skate-Thru in 2003.</p>
    <br>
    <h3>1989</h3>
    <p>The Ronald McDonald House Charities (RMHC) is incepted into Singapore, with the singular mission of directly improving the health and well-being of Singaporean children.</p>
    <br>
    <h3>1991</h3>
    <p>McDonalds introduces playgrounds to its premises, becoming one of the first restaurants to introduce a playground on its premises, allowing families to have fun and create memories together.</p>
    <br>
    <h3>1992</h3>
    <p>McDonalds introduces nutritional information on their menus in support of the Singapore’s National Healthy Lifestyle campaign. McDonalds offered an Eat Light Menu offering under-500 calorie meals.</p>
    <br>
    <h3>1995</h3>
    <p>The McSpicy is created and debuts in Singapore, having become a Singaporean favourite ever since its creation.</p>
